Nigerian singer and songwriter Ariyo Awodele Ezekiel aka Areezy, has announced plans to release an Elongated Play after the release of his lead single, ‘Gbagbe.’ Areezy kicked off the year 2022 with Gbagbe, the first single off his long-awaited EP Sonic Trip, a 6-track body of work.   Shady Blue admits to using COVID-19 to her advantage     Sekinat Usman completes Idamu Adugbo     BYT accuses Burna Boy, Wizkid of hijacking title of project   He also revealed that the EP will be released on April 1, 2022. The afro-fusion singer known for his unique heavily worded traditional afrobeat rhythm hinted on his Twitter page: “I want to take the world on a musical journey with my first EP, I hope that every song will help transport the listeners through whatever their struggles are and inspire a fresh burst of energy to go harder at whatever it is they desire.” The Prekers Entertainment poster boy got tipped as one of the new guards of Afrobeats, a shining light of the style Afro-fusion, a sound that combines elements of hip-hop, EDM, R&B, and African rhythms. SPONSORED